@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Installing"
@prev "Main"

                               @{b}@{fg shine}Introduction@{ub}@{fg text}                              
        ____________________________________________________________

                
        HTML-TEXT comes with ABSOLUTELY NO @{"WARRANTY" link "WARRANTY" 0} 
        This program is free software; you can redistribute it under 
        certain @{" conditions " link "Distribution" 0}.

@{b}About...@{ub}
                @{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} is a program that will take a 
        .html file and strip all marks from the file, it 
        will then write a new file that will contain the 
        plain text.

@{b}Features...@{ub}
               o@{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} uses a graphic user interface (GUI), so it 
                is easy to use.
               o@{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} can be used from the cli
               o@{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} features the use of locale.library and has 
                the following catalogs included:
                        
                        English builtin
                        @{b}Svenska by@{ub} @{fg shine}Roger Andersson@{fg text}
                        @{b}Deutsch by@{ub} @{fg shine}Daniel Amor@{fg text}
               
               o@{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} can keep href's in the text output.
               o@{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} can write an icon to the out file.
               
               Check the @{"reasons to register" link "Registering" 0}, for more features.

@{b}System Requirements...@{ub}

        Any Amiga with OS 2.x or above
@endnode

