@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Installing"

                                  @{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}
        _____________________________________________________________

                The operation of @{fg fill}HTML-TEXT@{fg text} is very straight forward, and
        any seasoned Amiga User should be capable of using the software
        right away.

@{b}File Options...@{ub}

        @{b}IN@{ub}: Click on this button and a load requester will open.
            Select the file you want to convert and click OK.
            You may also type in, the string gadget, the file to
            be converted.
       
       @{b}OUT:@{ub} Click on this button and a save requester will open.
            Enter the file name you want as the converted file.
            You may also type in, the string gadget, the file to
            be saved to.


@{b}Save Options...@{ub}

    @{b} HREF:@{ub} This is a checkmark gadget, and is used to keep those HREF's
           from an .html file in your converted text.
           As an example, lets say a file had this line of text+marks:
           
                @{fg highlight}You can reach him at <A HREF = "mailto:dloeser@iglou.com"> 
                dloeser@iglou.com</A>@{fg text}
        
           In the saved file you would see:
           
                @{fg highlight}You can reach him at [HREF = "mailto:dloeser@iglou.com"]
                dloeser@iglou.com@{fg text}
        
           The HREF is in side of the '[' and ']'
           If the gadget is not selected the above example would look like
           this, in your save file:
           
                @{fg highlight}You can reach him at dloeser@iglou.com@{fg text}
           
    @{b} ICON:@{ub} This gadget allows the save file to be saved with an icon.
           The icon has its default tool set to SYS:utilities/MultiView
            Convert...

           After selecting an in file and a out file you can click CONVERT
           and the .html file will be converted to text. There is a
progress
           bar there to let you know the status.

@{b}?...@{ub}
           This is the about gadget... you don,t have to read it.

@{b}Quit...@{ub}

           If your finished...
@endnode

