@node "CLI USAGE" "CLI USAGE"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"

                             @{u}@{fg shine}C L I   U S A G E@{uu}@{fg text}

        @{i}NEW for version 1.8!!!!@{ui}
        
        To run HTML-TEXT from the cli just type the following:
        
                1> HTML-TEXT <@{fg fill}infile_name@{fg text}> <(optional)@{fg fill}outfile_name@{fg text}>
                
        HTML-TEXT will automaticly create a file in your RAM: directory with
infile_name.txt
        as the extension.
        
        If you want to name the file and path to create then just pass this
as the outfile_name:
        
                1> HTML-TEXT <@{fg fill}infile_name@{fg text}> <path:@{fg fill}outfile_name@{fg text}>
                
        @{fg shine}As a bonus you can add HTML-TEXT to a  DOpus user menu like so:@{fg text}

                AmigaDOS PATH:HTML-TEXTv1.8 {f}{Rs}
        
        Thats it!!!!
@endnode

